<p><a name="Land_ownership" id="Land_ownership"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=British_Mandate_of_Palestine&amp;action=edit&amp;section=22" title="Edit section: Land ownership">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Land ownership</span></h2>
<p>As of 1931, the territory of the British Mandate of Palestine was 26,625,600 <a href="/wiki/Dunam" title="Dunam">dunums</a>, of which 8,252,900 dunums or 33% were arable.<sup id="cite_ref-99" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-99" title=""><span>[</span>100<span>]</span></a></sup>Official statistics show that Jews privately and collectively owned 1,393,531 dunums of land in 1945.<sup id="cite_ref-100" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-100" title=""><span>[</span>101<span>]</span></a></sup> Estimates of the total volume of land that Jews had acquired by 15 May 1948 are complicated by illegal and unregistered land transfers, as well as by the lack of data on land concessions from the Palestine administration after 31 March 1936.<sup id="cite_ref-101" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-101" title=""><span>[</span>102<span>]</span></a></sup> According to Avneri, Jews held 1,850,000 dunums of land in 1947.<sup id="cite_ref-102" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-102" title=""><span>[</span>103<span>]</span></a></sup> Stein gives the estimate of 2,000,000 dunums as of May 1948.<sup id="cite_ref-103" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-103" title=""><span>[</span>104<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><a name="Land_ownership_by_district" id="Land_ownership_by_district"></a></p>
